fields.comment: 9am start at Adrian's request. 3 hours at home to sew and repair library green stool
2 hours at home to repair vinyl on orange library stools
2 hrs at home to weld and rebuild dog tip

Irrigator recondition:  * file to sharpen worn and burred teeth on 60 tooth cog (5 hrs)  * rebuild worn tip of top/push dog  * replace drum wheel bush  * replace bottom shaft bushes  * replace missing grease nipples  * change wheels to level (?)  * grease, run and tune  To do:  * replace bottom/hold dog bush (unavalible at the time)  * rebuild and shape bottom/hold dog tip
2 hrs at home researching manuals and emailing contacts for taking on new responsibilites.
After work meeting with Gavin and Jon At home research ladder purchase online
5:30 finish 2 hrs with Maria on Saturday tidying front gardens and staff carpark At home: repair stool and fabricate handle for art room
9 - 5pm  Adrian simply took his last day off without a word.
6am - 6pm  1.5 hrs at home on computer communicating and ordering.
6pm - 6:30pm  And again time at home answering emails.
6am - 5pm  Very wet day, more relaxed, part of the day spent working on tidying and organising caretaker's workshop. Lot of help from Maria.
6am - 6:30pm  Maria assist with sweeping and gardening
6am - 5pm  Time at home emailing cleaner supplies order.  A vehicle had been out on the field overnight and damage to irrigation caused.
6am - 6pm  Frustrating to find myself spending so much time responding to damage caused by lack of thought and supervision - especially in gym space.
6am - 5:30pm  Home at computer for an hour or so replying emails and making cleaner order.

6am - 6pm  Extra rubbish on lock up. Hall stage left cluttered and has been hired out for Sunday.  Went in on Saturday to mow field, move irrigator and prepare gardens as requested at hall for prizegiving.  Went in again on Sunday to open hall for hirer, cleared chairs from stage, cleared gym equipment from gym, pulled out (and restored) stage. Finished mowing main field.  Maria and I did 6 hrs each on the weekemd.
6am - 5:30  Again extra rubbish in B block

8am - 5:30pm  Lots of unproductive time today providing simple services to staff, also time wasted answering non-events from cleaners.  In on Sunday for an hour because the CableNet man had got his master key stuck in a lock. I rescued him, dismantled the lock, extracted the key and straightened it. Bent keys catch in locks.
7:30am - 5pm  I had to chase up the master key - CableNet finished the job but the key was not returned to me. I need it Tuesday for the Rhino service check.

8am - 5:30pm  - to meet Bevan and discuss spraying on Tuesday - quoted for payground bark chip - Harkerss still unreachable (holiday?) - RockGas to remove 2 cylinders - nop skip pick up for 2 weeks despite my reminders both Thursdays
6am - 5:30pm  Home at 6pm, write emails, return to school at 7pm to open health centre for parent meeting

6am - 6pm  Today's dispointments:  * having to clean paint from pavement and wall - only to see it done again by the end of the day * ongoing battle to keep sprinklers in place - find them turned upside down, on the path, up trees, etc. * a rubbish bin filled with water * field was nicely picked of rubbish (not a disapointment) but no-one thought to look around the playground and tennis court  On the whole I found the kids wilder and more prone to playing up today. It seemed like all day lunchtime around the school.
6am - 6:30pm  No storage space for new desks and therefore obliged to deliver to room.
6am - 6pm  And an hour in the evening to write report on alarms
6am - 5pm  At home email, find stuff online, paper4trees, and building plan.
6am - 6pm  And then again stuff at home
Building plan, test and tag software, walk about.
6am - 6:30pm  Late finish so Maria could finish mowing the field before weather gets wet again.
6am - 5:30pm  Now spending around 1/2 hr/day securing hall complex at interval, lunch, and 3:10pm
I worked after time until 5:30; tidied, pruned and weeded the herb garden. Mulched with compost from home.
Term break begins.  Adrian vanished shortly after 10am and reappeared at 2pm. Does he actually do anything?
Adrian gone by 11am, back at 1:30pm. Anything acheived Adrian?
4:30 finished and cleaned up. Again no access to caretakers hovel so clean up in teachers facilities.
started 0530 to ensure boiler operation (not necessary as it turned out), took two tea breaks
worked 0600-1700 with two tea breaks (rain all day)
worked 0600-1730 with two tea breaks  This is the first time the caretakers rooms have had a proper clean. I've swept a few times but never seen it cleaned.
FInish 4:30 with extra rubbish and clear herb garden
worked 9am-3pm, early start to put away stage
Adrian sick - worked split shift, 8 hrs
Plus several hours on the weekend to weld, repair and prime basketball hoop and to repair broken tap fitting.
late finish to clear toilet for Bernadette
2 hrs at home to weld and repair tennis net strainer mechanisms
2 hrs at home to weld complete tennis net repair and outrigger for marking athletic track curves

annual leave - 5 hours to clean and repair line marker, repaired alumium inner wheel and saddle, built bracket and axle to carry new set of front wheels to add greater stability (with great success)    Hoe and weed beds witht Maria - as many as we could get to including admin, anzac, common areas.
